The paper deals with distributed machine learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus of the paper is on learning from decentralized features, which involves distributed optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with distributed computing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves data confidentiality, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
